text.paragraph:
See the Enbrel (etanercept) “Instructions for Use” insert for detailed information on injection site selection and dose administration [see Dosage and Administration (

                              2.3

                           ) and Patient Counseling Information (

                              17

                           )].

In addition to the 50 mg twice weekly recommended starting dose, starting doses of 25 mg or 50 mg per week were shown to be efficacious.  The proportion of responders was related to Enbrel dosage [
                           see
                            
                           Clinical Studies (

                              14.5

                           )
                           ].

The following components contain dry natural rubber (a derivative of latex), which may cause allergic reactions in individuals sensitive to latex: the needle cover of the prefilled syringe, the needle cover within the white cap of the SureClick autoinjector, and the needle cover within the purple cap of the Enbrel Mini cartridge [see Warnings and Precautions (

                              5.7

                           )].

Prior to initiating Enbrel and periodically during therapy, patients should be evaluated for active tuberculosis and tested for latent infection [see Warnings and Precautions (

                              5.1

                           )].

